➜Presentation和Essay类书面作业差异
http://www.sohu.com/a/416731353_490529	22559
<p>不论是写essay写到头秃的留学党，还是国内大学的被考试周折磨的学生们，都有过<strong>要用英语来进行所学专业课程研究的presentation的经历吧——</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/images01/20200906/0a2398c3d35444548b77d9a74f789096.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>往事不堪回首，相信大家在准备时<strong>都多少有过这样的苦恼：</strong></p>
<p>正式的学术类pre的模版是什么样的呢？</p>
<p>我的英语发音不好，不敢上台发表怎么办呀？</p>
<p>专业性很强的报告，我的口语会不会太大白话了?</p>
<p>还有很多同学上台尝试，只是把PPT上的研究内容宣读一遍，还使用<strong>自创的中式英文</strong>，难以达到学术交流的目的。</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p5.itc.cn/images01/20200906/9e65cecf36c44e849ef2ddfc0978a213.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>但是不用担心看完这个系列，<strong>这些问题统统都能搞定</strong>！</p>
<p><strong>目录：口语报告和书面论文的差异</strong></p>
<p>▲ 表达口语化</p>            <div class="lookall-box">
<div class="lookall-shadow"></div>
<section class="lookall">
<a href="javascript:;" class="show-all" id="showMore">
<em>展开全文</em>
</a>
</section>
</div>
<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p>▲ 常用主动语态</p>
<p>▲ 常用人称代名词</p>
<p>▲ 少用名词片语</p>
<p>▲ 少用复杂句</p>
<p>▲ 语调扮演重要角色</p>
<h1>Part<strong>1.表达口语化</strong></h1>
<p>★ 主要形式 ★</p>
<ul>
<li> 回溯 (backtracking)</li>
<li> 赘语 (redundancy)</li>
<li> 自我修正 (self-correction)</li>
<li> 简化形式 (reduced forms)</li>
<li> 使用许多填补语 (filler) 如um, uh, well, okay, like, anyway, you know, all right</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>💖举个例子：</strong></p>
<p><strong>Who’s gonna give me a definition of learning strategies?</strong></p>
<p>Who’s是Who is的缩写</p>
<p>Gonna是连音表达going to</p>
<p>其他如won’t=will not、cuz= because;wanna=want to、gotta =got to、outta=out of) </p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p0.itc.cn/images01/20200906/ba25cdf433b445f4aa53ee3ee66724c5.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>★ 实例 ★</p>
<p>以下一段话出自MICASE语料库的student presentation记录文本，大家看一下这位美国本土学生在作报告时，使用了哪些<strong>口头化表达。（用黄颜色标出）更多presentation技巧：www.12y.org</strong></p>
<p><strong>Okay</strong>, now basically this is <strong>uh</strong>, a study on <strong>um</strong>, <strong>I wanted to look at um</strong>, the bilingual population here at the University of Michigan, <strong>and I</strong> started out thinking<strong> I would just look at</strong>, whatever people I could find who were bilingual, <strong>and then I</strong> realized that it would be difficult to <strong>kind of</strong>, find anything out about it if I was just looking at whatever languages I came up with. <strong>So</strong> I ended up concentrating on two different languages, <strong>and um</strong>, I also concentrated on the easiest samples I could find, so I have a Spanish <strong>um</strong>, English bilingual sample, taken from a class actually of self identifying U-S Latinos. <strong>So that's something to consider, and then I have um</strong>, a sample from, <strong>a Hindi class, uh two Hindi classes actually here</strong>, which are mostly bilingual <strong>um</strong> heritage speakers of Hindi, or another Indian language.</p>
<h1>Part2.常用主动语态</h1>
<p><strong>🌟 书面语-被动</strong>: </p>
<p>A fiber-optic-based communications system is being installed by us this year.</p>
<p><strong>🌟口语-主动</strong>:</p>
<p>We are installing a fiber-optic- based communications system this year.</p>
<h1>Part3.人称代词</h1>
<p><strong>✨书面论文 </strong></p>
<p>为强调论述的客观性，作者常用 the author, the researcher, the research team等来指自己，以及 用readers指读者。 </p>
<p><strong>✨口头报告</strong></p>
<p>因和观众是面对面，就需用第一人称I或we指自己，用you 指观众。</p>
<h1>Part4.少用名词短语</h1>
<p><strong>例一</strong></p>
<p><strong>书面语:</strong></p>
<p>the application of....</p>
<p>for a considerable length of time ... is of considerable importance</p>
<p><strong>口语:</strong></p>
<p>to apply ...</p>
<p>for a long time</p>
<p>... is very important</p>
<p><strong>例二</strong></p>
<p><strong>书面语:</strong></p>
<p>This familiarity sprang in part from the long standing interest in the operation of government and in policy issues among academics and researchers. Studies which had originally developed out of the work of political scientists, economists and others were now embraced by the emerging policy analysis perspective. (Ham &amp; Hill, 1984) </p>
<p><strong>口语:</strong></p>
<p>It was familiar, because academics and researchers had been interested for a long time in how governments operate, and how people decide on policy. Political scientists, economists, and other people had studied these things, and now they were taken up by people who were interested in analyzing policy. (Hammond,1990)</p>
<h1>Part5.少用复杂句</h1>
<p>复杂句可能会增加听者的理解负担，<strong>尽量少用从属从句(subordinate clause)、关系从句 (relative clause) 等句构，</strong>改用对等的连接词如and, but等</p>
<p><strong>例一：</strong></p>
<p>All ten subjects who took part in visual inspection tasks for the experiment were provided with preliminary information before running the experiment.</p>
<p>观众要从ten subjects听到动词were provided with，中间有太多信息要消化，但口头表达稍纵即逝，所以不易听懂。</p>
<p><strong>例二：</strong></p>
<p>We had ten subjects, and they all took part in visual inspection tasks for our experiment. Then we provided them with preliminary information before doing this experiment.</p>
<p>前一句改成两句。第一句删除who，改用对等连接and连接两个子句。第二句被动语态were provided with 改成主动。</p>
<p><strong>例三</strong></p>
<p><strong>书面:</strong>Written in exact scientific terms, the project can demonstrate expertise and membership in the discourse community.</p>
<p><strong>口语:</strong> Because the project is written in exact scientific terms, it can demonstrate expertise and membership in the discourse community.</p>
<p>书面论文使用分词句型可精简信息。但口语报告时少用，应加上连接词和重复相同指代的主词。</p>
➜语调 (intonation) 在presentation中的重要性
http://www.sohu.com/a/416731838_490529	22870
<p>口语不像书面文本，有标点符号，转折与和连接词，<strong>必须借助音调的高低起伏和快慢来传达和诠释信息</strong>，如果留学生在做presentation的时候从头到尾只是平淡的语调，观众可能会感到疲乏，而抓不到重点。</p>
<p><strong>发音清晰与口音（accent）是两个不同概念</strong>，全世界有许多不同的口音，口音是国家人民建构语言身份和文化认同中的重要构成。我们受众母语影响，难免会说带有中文口音的英语，不过学习英语并不是为了去除母语口音，也不是为了成为英语母语者，而是让外国人理解清楚我们的想法，同时保留身为中国人的身份认同，<strong>所以做报告时要注意英语的发音正确，但无需过于担心中文口音的问题。</strong></p>
<p>以下是具体的<strong>一些语音语调注意事项</strong>：</p>
<p><strong>01长短音节的不同</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center">beach– bitch</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">deep– dip</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">each– itch feel– fill</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">age– edge</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">late– let</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">later– letter</p>
<p class="ql-align-center">mace– mess</p>
<p><strong>02重音 (stress)</strong></p>
<p><strong> 重音可分两种：</strong></p>
<p>①单词本身的重音音节 (stressed syllables)</p>
<p>②句子中哪些字需要加重音 (stressed words) 来强调其重要性 </p>
<p>A<strong>单字的重音节</strong></p>
<p>例：eighteen percent – eighty person ?</p>
<p><strong>字尾为__ical:</strong></p>
<p>通常重音落在 此音节的前一个音节，也可说是整个字的倒数第三个音节 biological， dialectical， diametrical，electrical</p>
<p><strong>字尾为__ity:</strong></p>
<p>通常重音落在此 音节的前一个音节，也可说是整个字的倒数第三个音节，举例 ：ability， accessibility， authenticity， civility</p>            <div class="lookall-box">
<div class="lookall-shadow"></div>
<section class="lookall">
<a href="javascript:;" class="show-all" id="showMore">
<em>展开全文</em>
</a>
</section>
</div>
<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p><strong>字尾为__logy:</strong></p>
<p>通常指学科名称，重音落在此音节的前一个音节，也就是整个字的倒数第三个音节 (MP3. 17) aerology，anthropology，archeology， biology</p>
<p>B<strong>词性不同产生的重音差异</strong></p>
<p>英语许多字同时具备不同的词性，例如record就具有名词（纪录）和动词（记录）两种词性。</p>
<p>这些字常会因其<strong>词性不同</strong>而产生发音和意义上的差异，尤其是重音和元音的改变。</p>
<p><strong>名词与动词</strong></p>
<p>abstract (n.摘要) – abstract (v.使抽象）</p>
<p>addict(n.上瘾的人) – addict (v.使成瘾) </p>
<p>address (n.地址) – address (v.称呼) </p>
<p>attribute(n.属性) – attribute (v.归因)</p>
<p>alternation (n.交替) alternate (v.交替) alternative (adj.替代的)</p>
<p>analog (n. 类比) / analogy (n.类比) analogize (v.类推)analogous (adj. 类似的)</p>
<p>analysis (n.分析) /analyst (n.分析师) analyze (v.分析)analytic (adj.分析的)</p>
<p>C<strong>句子中的重音字</strong></p>
<p>除了念对单词的重音节之外，还要注意句子<strong>中有哪些字是需要重读：</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>具有实质意义的内容字（content words）</strong>，例如动词、名词和修饰用的形容词或副词，它们承载文中的重要意义信息，需要重读。</li>
<li><strong>功能字如助动词、介词、冠词、连接词</strong>等通常不需重读。</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>较佳的重音字</strong></p>
<p>It is believed that the corpus callosum is involved in self- awareness and intelligence.</p>
<p><strong>欠佳的重音字</strong></p>
<p>It is believed that the corpus callosum is involved in self- awareness and intelligence.</p>
<p><strong>03停顿</strong></p>
<p><strong>根据语块（chunks）来：</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>以<strong>有意义的语块</strong>为单位说出</li>
<li>每个句子结束的句号，要完全停顿</li>
<li>句中如有逗号、分号以及名词片语介系词片语、子句或有完整意义语块处则可稍加停顿</li>
<li>但不宜停顿太多或停顿在错误的地方，使人不易理解</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>较佳的停顿</strong></p>
<p>In fact, / Dr. Brown and his colleagues found that/ the corpus callosum continues growing into the teen years. </p>
<p><strong>欠佳的停顿</strong></p>
<p>In fact, Dr. Brown and his / colleagues found that the corpus callosum continues / growing into the teen years. </p>
<p><strong>04关于语调</strong></p>
<p><strong>语调方面，</strong>陈述句语调的基本模式是<strong>先上升再下降</strong>，随着句子的开展逐渐将语调提高，碰到重要的内容字如名词和动词时还加重音量，直到句尾时再降低语调，提示观众这句话已经结束。助动词或be动词开头的封闭性疑问句，则句尾尾音的语调则会提高，突出该问题仍需解决或未完的语气。</p>
<p><strong>05关于语速</strong></p>
<p><strong>语速方面</strong>，非英语母语人士在口语报告时每分钟约90个字，<strong>也就是在20分钟的报告内大约要说1,800个字。</strong>报告时若能<strong>呈现快慢不同的说话节奏</strong>，比较能维持观众的兴趣，而且说话的速度也可以凸显内容的重点。特别是讲到内容中比较重要的地方应该把速度放慢，可以吸引观众的注意力并提示重点。</p>
<p>以上就是meeloun小编为大家整理的关于语调 (intonation) 在presentation中的重要性的问题，希望对大家有用。如果有需要presentation写作需要，请联系meeloun论文网(www.lxws.net)</p>